## рҹ“Ҡ Key Results

### **Detection Comparison (Top 5 Attacks)**

| Attack Type | Splunk | Sentinel | Wazuh | ELK | Best SIEM |
|-------------|--------|----------|-------|-----|-----------|
| RDP Brute Force | вң… Real-time | вң… Real-time | вң… Real-time | вҡ пёҸ 1min delay | Splunk/Sentinel |
| PowerShell Obfuscation | вң… Context-aware | вң…вң… Best context | вҡ пёҸ Generic alert | вҡ пёҸ Needs tuning | **Sentinel** |
| 0/70 VT Malware | вң… Behavioral | вң…вң… Best correlation | вҡ пёҸ Partial | вқҢ Missed | **Sentinel** |
| Lateral Movement (RDP) | вң… Detected | вң…вң… Identity context | вң… Detected | вҡ пёҸ Manual work | **Sentinel** |
| Mimikatz (Memory) | вң… Sysmon Event 10 | вң… Sysmon Event 10 | вң… Sysmon Event 10 | вң… Sysmon Event 10 | Tied |

**Winner:** Microsoft Sentinel (best out-of-box behavioral correlation)  
**Runner-up:** Splunk (best query flexibility, fastest)  
**Best Open-Source:** Wazuh (real-time, easy deployment)  

